<!-- KEY RISKS -->
<section>
  <div class="sec-label">Risks Worth Knowing</div>
  <div class="main-grid">
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-title">Savannah STR Regulation Risk</div>
      <div style="font-size:12px; color:var(--muted); line-height:1.6;">
        Savannah limits Airbnb to designated overlay districts with per-ward caps. If rules tighten — which is common in tourist cities — your Airbnb income could shrink or disappear. The mortgage still gets paid either way. <strong style="color:var(--ink)">Buy in the overlay district intentionally, and have a plan B: long-term rental at ~$1,800/mo covers most of the mortgage.</strong>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-title">The Rate Gamble</div>
      <div style="font-size:12px; color:var(--muted); line-height:1.6;">
        If you buy in 2036 and rates are still 6.5%+, your mortgage payment is higher but the math still works with Airbnb income. If rates drop to 5% or below — refinance immediately. Every 1% drop on $360K saves you ~$215/month for the life of the loan.
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-title">Climate & Insurance</div>
      <div style="font-size:12px; color:var(--muted); line-height:1.6;">
        Savannah has real flood and hurricane exposure. Flood insurance is separate from HOI and could run $800–2,000+/yr depending on flood zone. <strong style="color:var(--ink)">Factor this into your offer price and property selection.</strong> This is non-negotiable before buying.
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-title">Down Payment Gap</div>
      <div style="font-size:12px; color:var(--muted); line-height:1.6;">
        Your financial plan targets ~$80K for a house fund by 40. A $450K Savannah home needs $90K (20%) to avoid PMI, or $45K (10%) with PMI. <strong style="color:var(--ink)">The $10K gap is closeable — about $83/mo extra over 10 years — or you go in at 10% down and eliminate PMI once you hit 20% equity.</strong>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="note">
    <p><strong>Georgia Dream Program:</strong> Georgia offers down payment assistance programs for qualifying buyers. <strong>As of June 2026, the Georgia Dream rate is 5.75%</strong> — meaningfully better than market rate. Worth investigating closer to your purchase date.</p>
  </div>
</section>

